-# Instead of populating this field with the content of the page part, we get
-# the association IDs directly from the page itself (with some safety for new
-# records.) Since this is an actual association, the content of the page part
-# itself should be considered superfluous.
-# A complete implementation would present a user-friendly page selection
-# interface instead of just exposing the IDs.

.row
  = text_field_tag "page[parts_attributes][#{page_part_counter}][content]", @page.try(:related_page_ids).try(:join, ',')